video_identification.title: Palestine Museum US Conversation with Salman Abu Sitta

extracted_metadata.title: Palestine Museum US Conversation with Salman Abu Sitta
extracted_metadata.description: Palestinian historian and cartographer, Salman Abu-Sitta, discusses his new book "Atlas of Palestine 1871-1877" and its historical significance in documenting and preserving the state of Palestinian maps, towns, and and populations prior to the Zionist colonization of Palestine. July 12, 2020
